<!-- Hero --------------------------------------------------------------- -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="inner">
    <span class="eyebrow">Section 01 · Strategy</span>
    <h1 class="display">
      What GritFuel <span class="accent">is</span>, and who it's for.
    </h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The foundations — the job we do, the customer we do it for, the founder profile we built around, and the size of the prize. If any of this is wrong, everything downstream needs to move.
    </p>
  </div>
  <img class="hero-arrow" src="assets/brand-assets/arrow-charcoal.png" alt="">
</section>

<!-- Narrative ---------------------------------------------------------- -->
<section class="band" style="padding-top: var(--s-8);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">The short story</span>
      <h2>A Growth Operating System for founders ready to scale.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        GritFuel is a monthly subscription that gives growth-led founders — start-ups, scale-ups, and companies in transformation — a structured way to build, test, and optimise growth, without hiring a CMO or piecing together five agencies. Two test markets at go-live: the Netherlands (€500k – €5m revenue) and South Africa (R5M – R100M revenue), chosen because we have depth of relationships in both. The core thesis: growth is a system, not a campaign, and most founders at this stage don't have the operating model to run one.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over the past weeks we've pressure-tested the positioning, mapped the customer, and sized the market. The four artefacts below are the output of that work. Start with the Business Model Canvas for the one-pager, then open the JTBD / Value Proposition Canvas to see how we're framing the customer's job, and the Founder DeepDive for the persona detail. The Market Size note grounds the whole thing in numbers.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Key decisions -->
    <div class="section-head" style="margin-top: var(--s-8);">
      <span class="eyebrow">Key decisions</span>
      <h2>What's locked, what's open.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="decisions">
      <div class="decision locked">
        <div class="marker"></div>
        <div class="body">
          <h4>Category: "Growth Operating System" — not agency, not SaaS</h4>
          <p>We are deliberately not positioning against agencies or tool vendors. The category is systems-led, subscription-based, and founder-facing.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="status">Locked</span>
      </div>
      <div class="decision open">
        <div class="marker"></div>
        <div class="body">
          <h4>ICP: start-ups, scale-ups, and companies in transformation — NL (€500k – €5m) and SA (R5M – R100M) as first test markets</h4>
          <p>Too early and there's no revenue to optimise; too late and they have in-house growth teams. Two test geographies, not one: <strong>NL</strong> (BV structure, local network, €500k – €5m AR) and <strong>SA</strong> (relationships we already have, R5M – R100M AR — a downscaled band to match the local curve). Ranges want pressure-testing against real pipeline; treating this as open until we have cohort-one signal.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="status">Open</span>
      </div>
      <div class="decision open">
        <div class="marker"></div>
        <div class="body">
          <h4>Beachhead vertical — still open</h4>
          <p>Leaning toward consumer DTC and vertical SaaS. Want your read on whether to go narrow or stay horizontal for the first cohort.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="status">Open</span>
      </div>
      <div class="decision open">
        <div class="marker"></div>
        <div class="body">
          <h4>Anchor JTBD phrasing — needs a second pass</h4>
          <p>Current working job statement is in the JTBD canvas. The language is close but not quite right. Feedback welcome.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="status">Open</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Artefacts ---------------------------------------------------------- -->
<section class="band" style="padding-top: 0;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">The artefacts</span>
      <h2>Open these in order.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="artefacts">

      <!-- 1. BMC -->
      <article class="artefact">
        <span class="tag html">HTML · Canvas</span>
        <h3>Business Model Canvas</h3>
        <p class="desc">The one-page summary: value propositions, customer segments, channels, revenue streams, cost structure. Strategyzer format.</p>
        <p class="look"><strong>Look at:</strong> the Value Propositions block — check whether the language there holds up against your reading of the customer.</p>
        <div class="links">
          <a class="btn" href="artefacts/GritFuel_Business_Model_Canvas_v1.html" target="_blank">Open canvas →</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- 2. JTBD / VPC -->
      <article class="artefact">
        <span class="tag html">HTML · Canvas</span>
        <h3>JTBD &amp; Value Proposition Canvas</h3>
        <p class="desc">The customer's job, pains, and gains — mapped against our product's pain relievers and gain creators. The "why they'd buy" document.</p>
        <p class="look"><strong>Look at:</strong> the Pain–Pain Reliever fit column. Flag any pain we're claiming to solve that you don't think we actually do.</p>
        <div class="links">
          <a class="btn" href="artefacts/GritFuel_JTBD_VPC_v1.html" target="_blank">Open canvas →</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- 3. Founder DeepDive -->
      <article class="artefact">
        <span class="tag html">HTML · Persona</span>
        <h3>Founder / CEO DeepDive</h3>
        <p class="desc">A rich persona document for the buyer: context, priorities, fears, information diet, and how they make a "yes" decision on something like this.</p>
        <p class="look"><strong>Look at:</strong> the "Decision triggers" section — this is what we're betting GTM copy and onboarding around.</p>
        <div class="links">
          <a class="btn" href="artefacts/GritFuel_FounderCEO_DeepDive_v2.html" target="_blank">Open persona →</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- 4. Market Size -->
      <article class="artefact">
        <span class="tag html">HTML · Analysis</span>
        <h3>Market Sizing (TAM / SAM / SOM)</h3>
        <p class="desc">A bottom-up sizing of the post-seed SME segment in NL + wider EU. Assumptions are explicit and easy to challenge. Note: current doc is EU-first — an SA sizing addendum is on the list once the SA revenue band is pressure-tested.</p>
        <p class="look"><strong>Look at:</strong> the SOM assumption set — this is where the biggest margin of error sits. Gut-check the capture rate.</p>
        <div class="links">
          <a class="btn" href="artefacts/market_size_v1.html" target="_blank">Open analysis →</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- 5. PMF (optional doc download) -->
      <article class="artefact">
        <span class="tag doc">DOCX · Supporting</span>
        <h3>PMF Assessment &amp; Positioning Recommendations</h3>
        <p class="desc">Supporting document that informed the positioning and category calls. Optional reading — the canvases above are the primary source.</p>
        <p class="look"><strong>Look at:</strong> section 3 — "Positioning Recommendations" — if you only have 5 minutes.</p>
        <div class="links">
          <a class="btn ghost" href="downloads/GritFuel — PMF Assessment &amp; Positioning Recommendations.docx" download>Download .docx</a>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Asks --------------------------------------------------------------- -->
<section class="band" style="padding-top: 0;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="asks">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--lime);">What I need from you</span>
      <h3>Four specific questions on Strategy.</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Geographies + ranges:</strong> NL €500k – €5m and SA R5M – R100M as parallel test markets — does that split hold, or do we start NL-only and phase SA in after cohort one? If parallel, what shifts in the SA range?</li>
        <li><strong>Beachhead:</strong> do we go narrow (one vertical — consumer DTC or vertical SaaS) for cohort one, or stay horizontal? What's your instinct and why?</li>
        <li><strong>JTBD phrasing:</strong> after reading the canvas, does the current job statement land for you, or is it still abstract? If abstract — what would you sharpen?</li>
        <li><strong>SOM:</strong> the capture assumption in the Market Size note is aggressive on purpose. Push back if you think it's unrealistic for year one.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

